				<p>Maybe I will turn this into an answer later, but I think you generally have two options. The first is to pay quite a bit for a decent piece of software (SolidWorks and other CAD programs should be able to do what you want, but you'll probably have to pay even more than the base cost for the required modules). The second is to write your own code using open-source tools like [VTK](http://www.vtk.org/) and [Gazebo](http://gazebosim.org/). Gazebo is not too bad and will probably take care of all your visualization needs anyway (so you don't really need VTK).</p>
